29/07/2008
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Local media reported on Monday (July 28th) that Romania and Ukraine will settle a territorial dispute over the Serpents' Island at the International Court of Justice. The small island has natural resources of 100 billion cubic meters of natural gas and 10m tonnes of oil. The lawsuit also refers to the legal border of the island, an area covering about 12,000 square kilometres. (Hotnews, Adevarul, Mediafax - 28/07/08) 
